arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Abhinav Ramnarayan and Steven Arons re=
port</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The European Banking Authority has been holdin=
g talks on ways to boost investor interest in the AT1 market after Switzerl=
and=E2=80=99s shock decision to wipe out about $17 billion of Credit Suisse=
 Group AG notes.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The EBA earlier this month addressed ideas suc=
h as a ban on banks paying dividends before they consider skipping an AT1 c=
oupon to preserve capital during times of stress, people familiar with the =
matter said, asking not to be identified discussing the private information=
. Other ideas floated at an event held by the body included a requirement t=
o pay out skipped AT1 coupons at a later stage rather than allowing them to=
 be canceled altogether, the people said. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The price of issuing AT1 bonds is still elevat=
ed compared with levels before the Credit Suisse rescue. Their average yiel=
d in an index of European AT1 debt is currently above 11% =E2=80=94 almost =
twice the average coupon of roughly 6% on previously issued AT1 bonds, acco=
rding to data compiled by Bloomberg.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">These changes would make AT1s=C2=A0<em>less lo=
ss-absorbing</em>, which would be bad for their usefulness as bank capital,=
 but=C2=A0<em>more attractive to investors</em>, and if nobody buys them th=
en they=E2=80=99re not that useful anyway.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Incidentally my own view of the correct regula=
tory response here is something like =E2=80=9Cmemories in financial markets=
 are extremely short, and any time a bond investor indignantly huffs that s=
he will never buy some type of bond again, she=E2=80=99ll be buying it with=
in a week.=E2=80=9D You have a meeting with AT1 investors, they say =E2=80=
=9Cyou need to make sure that these bonds can never lose money,=E2=80=9D yo=
u nod and say =E2=80=9Cof course, of course,=E2=80=9D you wait six minutes,=
 you forget all about it. I am not sure that will work here but I don=E2=80=
=99t think I=E2=80=99d bet against it.</p>
