<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A panel tasked with overseeing the credit defa=
ult swaps market has ruled that the write down of=C2=A0Credit Suisse Group =
AG=E2=80=99s Additional Tier 1 notes will not trigger an insurance payout.=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Credit Derivatives Determinations Committe=
e (CDDC) determined at a meeting on Wednesday that the write down would not=
 lead to a payout of the default swaps tied to the bank=E2=80=99s subordina=
ted debt, according to a=C2=A0notice=C2=A0on its website. In reaching its d=
ecision, the committee took the view that the AT1 notes were in fact junior=
 to the subordinated bonds underlying the swaps.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course, but weirder things have happened an=
d it was worth a shot.</p>
