<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One thing that I have found, in writing about =
finance for a long time, is that financial scandals, crimes and disasters a=
re more fun=C2=A0<em>to write about</em> than stuff going well. Part of thi=
s is that the scandals often have stakes and drama, while everything going =
fine does not. Part of it is that much of normal finance is=C2=A0<em>secret=
ive =E2=80=94</em>=C2=A0if you have a good investment strategy or product y=
ou are not necessarily going to explain how it works =E2=80=94=C2=A0while t=
he scandals tend to produce lots of <em>public information</em>, in the for=
m of court filings. Part of it is that the scandals are often pretty funny;=
=C2=A0frauds tend to play on interesting quirks of human nature and financi=
al markets, and also the people doing the fraud often send=C2=A0each other =
entertaining=C2=A0emails about it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so, when some big financial scandal happen=
s, am I a bit gleeful? I am. Do I feel bad for the people who have lost the=
ir life savings in the fraud, and the people who might go to prison for doi=
ng it? I do. But I am gleeful for=C2=A0<em>me</em>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/31513959.263431/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vM=
jAyMy8wNS8xNi9ib29rcy9taWNoYWVsLWxld2lzLWZ0eC1iYW5rbWFuLWZyaWVkLWdvaW5nLWlu=
ZmluaXRlLmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa8cc737b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">an interview wit=
h Michael Lewis</a>, who has a new book coming out about Sam Bankman-Fried =
and the collapse of FTX. Lewis was spending a lot of time with Bankman-Frie=
d back when he was just a financial=C2=A0<em>success=C2=A0</em>story, a you=
ng self-made billionaire who was creating the future of finance. And then B=
ankman-Fried=C2=A0became a huge scandal, which worked out even better for L=
ewis:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>When he was arrested, did you worry th=
at it might blow up your book, or make it better?</strong></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I hate to say this. It=E2=80=99s horrible. It =
does not reflect well on me as a human being, but my first thought was, =E2=
=80=98Oh my God=E2=80=99 =E2=80=94 it was like a lock clicking into place =
=E2=80=94 =E2=80=98now I have the story.=E2=80=99 It didn=E2=80=99t occur t=
o me for a moment that it would blow up the book. I did think, just how mes=
sy is this going to get, as the writer, because I=E2=80=99d been so involve=
d. Nobody watched this the way I did, so, was I going to be dragged into th=
is in some way? But I=E2=80=99ve been allowed to do my job, and it=E2=80=99=
s been one of the most exciting creative experiences I=E2=80=99ve ever had.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>You=E2=80=99ve continued to visit Bank=
man-Fried. How has his legal situation affected your access to him, and do =
you feel he=E2=80=99s more guarded in his conversations with you?</strong><=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He=E2=80=99s the ideal subject. He=E2=80=99s l=
ocked up in his house an hour from my house with an ankle monitor. He can=
=E2=80=99t go anywhere. It=E2=80=99s unbelievably convenient, as long as th=
ey keep him there. So, as long as he welcomes me into the house, it=E2=80=
=99s fine. I=E2=80=99ve been seeing him roughly every two weeks.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He=E2=80=99s not wrong.</p>
